<br>
Take the 5-10 minutes of actual gameplay you get between FMV cutscenes and hour-long Codec conversations (what are they, 16 year old girls gossiping about the latest top secret dirt?) and turn them into yet more FMV cutscenes and hour-long Codec conversations.<br>
<br>
I swear, every @#%$ step I took I got another @#%$ beep on my Codec.<br>
<br>
Every time I went through a door there was a @#%$ cutscene.<br>
<br>
I'm playing to play.  If I wanted to watch a movie I would have rented that instead of MGS2.<br>
<br>
Whoever thinks the second one is better is dead wrong.  The first was by and far a hugely superior game.<br>
<br>
I will give it that the gameplay of the second is good... when it actually happens.  Oh, geeze, I missed that half-second run down the hallway between a Codec conversation and an FMV cutscene?  Sorry, I must have dozed off after they mentioned who the Russian soldiers/mercenaries were for the dozenth time in as many minutes.<br>
<br>
I can't even get over how unbelievably obnoxious and just outright stupid the HUGE amount of storyline-pushing elements are jam-packed into no game.<br>
<br>
Argh. <p>Houseless Rake of 52 Jests<br><a href="http://www.thesafehouse.org">Safehouse,</a> Ring Warden of The Rathe
